      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Configuration management, regression testing, and V&V documentation must meet MRL 5 SQA requirements per ASME V&V 40 Table 1.",
      "rationale": "SQA documentation exists for the commercial CFD solver but lacks device-specific regression test suite covering hemolysis constitutive model changes. Version control is present; formal change-impact analysis for hemolysis sub-model is absent. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions or equivalent must confirm order-of-accuracy for all governing equation terms including hemolysis transport equation.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy verification completed for Navier-Stokes solver (second-order confirmed). Hemolysis scalar transport equation verified only via comparison to semi-analytical solution on simplified geometry; full MMS not applied. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or GCI with at least three systematically refined grids; GCI below 5% for hemolysis QoI at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-level GCI study performed on FDA pump geometry. GCI for pressure head 2.1%; GCI for NIH 11.3% at design point, rising to 19.7% at off-design conditions. Boundary layer resolution insufficient near blade trailing edge under high-speed VAD conditions. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental conditions must replicate VAD operating envelope including hematocrit range 35–45%, temperature 37°C, and pulsatile inlet waveform representative of cardiac assist mode.",
      "rationale": "Available benchmark experiments used steady-state inlet conditions and hematocrit 40% only. Pulsatile VAD waveform not replicated. Temperature controlled at 37°C. Two of five required operating points lack experimental counterparts. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., validation metric per ASME V&V 20) must demonstrate model prediction within clinical acceptance band; systematic bias must be characterized.",
      "rationale": "Validation metric computed per ASME V&V 20 for NIH at three operating points. Systematic over-prediction of 23–47% observed. Clinical acceptance band (NIH < 0.005 g/100 L) not met by model predictions at two of three validated points. Bias source not isolated. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be identical to or directly translatable from the regulatory submission QoIs; no surrogate metrics accepted at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the direct regulatory QoI and is used in validation. However, validation dataset reports plasma-free hemoglobin by spectrophotometry while submission requires NIH normalized by pump flow and time; conversion introduces additional uncertainty not fully characterized. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must cover the full VAD operating envelope; geometry, fluid properties, and boundary conditions must match COU within defined similarity criteria.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic pump, not the specific VAD device. Geometric similarity established for impeller diameter and blade angle; volute geometry differs substantially. Fluid is bovine blood in validation vs. human blood in COU. Operating speed range partially overlaps (3000–5000 rpm validated; COU requires 2500–6000 rpm). Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria, floating-point round-off assessment, and solver residual monitoring must be documented for all simulations in the VAD operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored by residual drop to 1e-5; however, formal floating-point error analysis not performed. Solver error contribution to hemolysis prediction uncertainty not isolated from model form uncertainty in UQ campaign. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented review process for simulation setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing must demonstrate independence of at least one qualified reviewer.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup documented. Single analyst performed all pre-processing, execution, and post-processing. Use error contribution cannot be bounded. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for turbulence model selection, hemolysis constitutive law, and non-Newtonian rheology model must be provided with supporting validation evidence specific to VAD flow regimes.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected without VAD-specific justification. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) used despite known limitations at low shear rates present in VAD recirculation zones. Non-Newtonian effects modeled with Carreau-Yasuda fit to bovine blood, not human blood. Model form uncertainty not quantified separately in UQ campaign. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs must be characterized with probability distributions; epistemic uncertainty in material properties and boundary conditions must be distinguished from aleatory uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ campaign propagated uncertainty in 8 input parameters (inlet velocity profile, hematocrit, viscosity coefficients, hemolysis model exponents). Epistemic vs. aleatory distinction not formally made; all inputs treated as aleatory uniform or normal distributions. Geometric uncertainty from manufacturing tolerances not included. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples must be statistically characterized; sample size must be sufficient to estimate population mean NIH with 95% confidence interval width below 10% of the clinical threshold.",
      "rationale": "Experimental dataset comprises n=6 replicate measurements per operating point from a single laboratory. Statistical power analysis not performed. Inter-laboratory variability not characterized. Insufficient to bound population-level hemolysis with required confidence at MRL 5. Flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mapping between experimental input parameters and simulation boundary conditions must be formally documented; any discrepancies must be quantified and their impact on QoI bounded.",
      "rationale": "Inlet boundary conditions in simulation derived from bulk flow rate measurements; spatial velocity profile assumed fully developed parabolic, inconsistent with experimental pump inlet geometry. Rotational speed equivalency between experimental tachometer and CFD imposed speed not validated. Formal equivalency mapping document not produced. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    }
